Automated Backups:
Schedule regular backups using cron jobs on a Linux system.
bash
# Cron job for daily backups at midnight
0 0 * * * /usr/bin/mysqldump -u root -pYourPassword BookstoreDB > /path/to/backup/BookstoreDB_$(date +\%F).sql

Manual Backup:
Perform manual backups using the mysqldump command.
bash
mysqldump -u root -pYourPassword BookstoreDB > /path/to/backup/BookstoreDB.sql
